subject: Add the authenticate signal to SoupMessage
commitMessage:
Add the authenticate signal to SoupMessage

We are getting the following error message while browsing the Web on MiniBrowser
because Tizen webkit2-efl needs the authenticate signal of SoupMessage, but this signal was added to Tizen2.1.

"(WebProcess:441): GLib-GObject-WARNING **: gsignal.c:2475: signal `authenticate' is invalid for instance `0xc399e70' of type `SoupMessage'"

comments.message:
Patch Set 1:

Why are you commenting out all the macros?

Patch Set 1:

We don't have TIZEN.h in libsoup in order to enable/disable the macro, so I just want to enable this signal by default.

Patch Set 1:

then basically we don't have the build option so lets not include comments for the phantom build option.
Uploaded patch set 2.
Uploaded patch set 3.
Patch Set 3: Verified+1 Code-Review+2
Change has been successfully merged into the git repository.

subject: Add glib-networking to the libsoup dependency requirements.
commitMessage:
Add glib-networking to the libsoup dependency requirements.

glib-networking needs to be installed with libsoup in order to support SSL/TLS.

comments.message:
Patch Set 1:

Since there are no other libsoup changes in the works then please add a changelog entry to this and also us gbs to submit so when the change is excepted it will result in the build being updated

Patch Set 1:

Is this right step?

$ gbs ch
$ git add libsoup.changes
$ git commit -m "Update changelog for new release"
$ gbs submit

Patch Set 1:

almost... I am suggesting that you ammend this change to also include the changelog entry, so 'git commit --amend'

NOTE:  If you start adding change-id's to your commits then when you resubmit the same change then the change will show up as an additional patchset in the same review.  Since you didn't do that then you will need to abandon this review and the push will create a new review

Patch Set 1:

Documentation on change-id:

https://review.tizen.org/gerrit/Documentation/user-changeid.html
